1
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:34,640
There's over five million baht

2
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:36,600
in that safe.

3
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:39,040
Let's split it fairly,
half and half. Deal?

4
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:40,280
If you want our help.

5
00:01:40,360 --> 00:01:41,800
Why should I share it with you?

6
00:01:41,880 --> 00:01:43,080
Suit yourself.

7
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:46,880
Whoever gets it, gets it. Your call.

8
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:48,240
He really does love his mom.

9
00:01:48,320 --> 00:01:49,760
There it is. His weak spot.

10
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:52,440
<i>If he loves his mom that much,</i>
<i>we'll just kidnap her.</i>

11
00:01:52,520 --> 00:01:55,240
<i>Then make him pay ransom to get her back.</i>

12
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:56,160
Leave the money there.

13
00:01:56,240 --> 00:01:57,400
Then take your mom.

14
00:01:57,480 --> 00:02:00,240
After what you did to my mom,
I'm not letting you get away with this.

15
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:02,360
Throw it, or I shoot.

16
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:05,800
This world is dangerous.
It's nothing but hunters and prey.

17
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:08,360
What do you think you are? A hunter?

18
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:09,520
Or maybe just prey

19
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:11,920
fooling yourself into thinking
you're the hunter?

20
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:14,120
<i>Like I said,</i>

21
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:16,480
<i>magic isn't real sorcery.</i>

22
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:21,080
<i>All the tricks</i>
<i>we come up with to fool others,</i>

23
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:22,640
<i>often end up</i>

24
00:02:22,720 --> 00:02:24,760
- <i>fooling ourselves instead.</i>
- Thank you.

25
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:36,600
<i>Some people</i>

26
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:39,080
<i>fool themselves</i>
<i>into clinging to illusions,</i>

27
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:42,240
<i>even when those things</i>
<i>might never have existed.</i>

28
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:47,960
<i>Some try to build thick walls</i>

29
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:50,040
<i>to hide themselves</i>

30
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:53,200
- <i>and escape the real world.</i>
- Angpao!

31
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:54,120
Angpao!

32
00:02:56,960 --> 00:03:00,440
<i>Some believe no one</i>
<i>can keep up with their game.</i>

33
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:01,480
We're here.

34
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:03,760
<i>They think they're above everyone else.</i>

35
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:07,120
Honestly, there was no need to move me.

36
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:11,120
Mom, this place is bigger and safer.

37
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:12,800
Better than the old one.

38
00:03:12,880 --> 00:03:14,440
Let's go take a look.

39
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:17,920
<i>Even though they don't realize it,</i>

40
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:19,520
- <i>they are</i>
- It's so big!

41
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:21,600
<i>constantly running.</i>

42
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:25,480
<i>And many others</i>

43
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:28,840
<i>deceive themselves</i>
<i>by rushing to chase happiness.</i>

44
00:03:28,920 --> 00:03:31,120
<i>Because they know</i>

45
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:33,000
<i>life is short</i>

46
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:36,000
<i>and slipping away.</i>

47
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:40,640
<i>But the most painful self-deception</i>

48
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:44,160
<i>is fooling yourself</i>
<i>into thinking there's still hope.</i>

49
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:50,000
<i>And no matter how painful it gets,</i>

50
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:54,200
<i>we all try to hold on to hope.</i>

51
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:13,760
<i>Because deep down, we know</i>

52
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:16,279
<i>that if we lose it,</i>

53
00:04:16,959 --> 00:04:20,440
<i>there'll be nothing left</i>
<i>to hold onto.</i>

54
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:25,480
THREE YEARS EARLIER

55
00:04:41,280 --> 00:04:42,880
Doing this

56
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:45,120
doesn't count as caring for your friend.

57
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:48,080
If you let your friend
copy your answers like this again,

58
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:50,440
I'll fail you in every subject.

59
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:58,280
THE CLOSED CLASSROOM BY MAGICIAN

60
00:05:01,840 --> 00:05:02,880
WAITING FOR THE NEXT CHAPTER, MAGICIAN.

61
00:05:02,960 --> 00:05:04,040
LOVE EVERY STORY

62
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:05,200
FOR MYSTERIES AND INVESTIGATIONS
YOU'RE THE BEST, MAGICIAN

63
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:08,040
Hey!

64
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:12,160
Hey! Can't you hear me?

65
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:14,360
You were the one
who told the teacher about us, right?

66
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,640
What does that have to do with you?

67
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:21,000
I'm just telling the truth.

68
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:23,160
Right is right. Wrong is wrong.

69
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:26,440
Why? Can't stand what's wrong?

70
00:05:26,520 --> 00:05:28,880
If you admit it was wrong,

71
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:30,720
then I didn't do anything wrong, did I?

72
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:32,320
How did you grow up

73
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:34,840
thinking you have the right
to judge other people?

74
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:38,160
No wonder nobody wants to be around you.

75
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:40,760
Ris, enough. Let's go.

76
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:42,440
I hate people like that.

77
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:45,120
Arrogant, showing off,
always craving attention.

78
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:47,120
I want to know
what kind of world they come from.

79
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:48,440
Forget it. Come on.

80
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:52,160
No wonder Angpao turned out like this.

81
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:57,960
You think you can help your friend

82
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,560
and support them
for the rest of their life?

83
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:03,880
That's why fools stay fools.
They never learn to think for themselves.

84
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:07,600
Because people like you
keep helping them the wrong way.

85
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:08,560
You smart-mouth!

86
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:09,600
I think

87
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,840
instead of messing with other people,

88
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:14,000
you should fix your crappy novel first.

89
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:20,320
Let's go.

90
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:31,480
Sorry you got dragged into this
because of me.

91
00:06:32,120 --> 00:06:35,280
It's fine. Don't worry about it.
See you tomorrow.

92
00:06:50,760 --> 00:06:52,960
What's up? You here to apologize?

93
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,760
I'd apologize if I thought I was wrong.

94
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:58,480
But I don't.

95
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:08,240
Hey, wait. If you've got guts,
tell me what's wrong with my novel.

96
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:13,120
Why? You can't handle it?

97
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:19,720
I think you just can't answer.
I doubt you've even read my novel.

98
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:23,000
Pen name, Magician.

99
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:25,760
The most-read blog novel,

100
00:07:25,840 --> 00:07:28,440
"The Closed Classroom." Okay?

101
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:32,400
I don't judge a book by its cover
like you do.

102
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:35,400
Then answer me.

103
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:37,840
Fine.

104
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:41,880
Your novels are just like you,

105
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:45,160
always living in an ideal world.

106
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:48,040
You've never lived in the real world.

107
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:49,880
You sit there making things up,

108
00:07:49,960 --> 00:07:52,600
judging who's good or bad,

109
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:55,960
even though you've never really known
your characters at all.

110
00:07:57,560 --> 00:08:00,640
If my novels are that terrible,

111
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:01,880
why do so many people follow me?

112
00:08:01,960 --> 00:08:04,800
Just because something's popular
doesn't make it good.

113
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:08,160
I think you're just biased.

114
00:08:09,960 --> 00:08:12,360
So this is how you judge people?

115
00:08:12,440 --> 00:08:15,200
Anyone who thinks differently is biased?

116
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:17,600
People who aren't smart are idiots?

117
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:20,200
Anyone who does something wrong
is automatically evil?

118
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:23,040
Isn't that true?

119
00:08:24,760 --> 00:08:27,680
The world isn't just black and white,
you know.

120
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:32,559
Alright, let's test it.

121
00:08:50,560 --> 00:08:52,000
Three bags, Grandma.

122
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:12,560
Do you think
she's a good person or a bad one?

123
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:17,040
Hey, I'm not someone
who thinks poor people are bad.

124
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:18,600
I can't judge from this alone.

125
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:20,640
I have to see what she does first.

126
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:25,360
If she finds the wallet
and returns it to the station,

127
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:28,760
she's good. But if she steals
the money inside,

128
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,080
she's bad.

129
00:09:31,160 --> 00:09:33,080
Nothing left to ask, right?

130
00:09:34,760 --> 00:09:37,160
Alright, let's make a bet.

131
00:09:37,680 --> 00:09:39,240
Whether she's good or bad.

132
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:44,040
If you're wrong, I don't
have to pay back that 5,000.

133
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:55,240
MISS ARISA VARINSAWONG

134
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:58,040
This belongs to that young lady
from earlier.

135
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:02,520
I think she's bad.

136
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:19,720
KRUNGSRI BANK

137
00:10:44,760 --> 00:10:47,560
Still need to ask if she's good or bad?

138
00:10:48,640 --> 00:10:49,600
You're judging already?

139
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:52,080
Let's watch till the end.

140
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:12,200
That grandma's house is just up ahead.

141
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:14,920
How do you know?

142
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:19,000
I walk this way home.
I see her all the time.

143
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:23,080
Wait, you walk home
through here every day?

144
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:27,320
Only when I don't have money for the bus.

145
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:32,040
There's your "bad" grandma.

146
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:42,280
Come on.

147
00:12:20,280 --> 00:12:21,880
Here, share this and eat.

148
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:24,560
You bought so much, Grandma.

149
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:26,000
Take this too.

150
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:29,120
Did you win the lottery?

151
00:12:29,640 --> 00:12:31,240
Yeah.

152
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:34,920
When I have nothing,
you share with me too, alright?

153
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:37,720
Yes, Grandma. Thank you.

154
00:12:40,880 --> 00:12:42,440
Come on. Let's go inside.

155
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:55,480
I'm back, old man.

156
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:57,240
Let's go.

157
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:29,400
So, can you answer now?

158
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:31,520
Is she a good person or a bad one?

159
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:39,000
The world doesn't leave
poor people with many choices.

160
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:42,600
Some people

161
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:45,640
do bad things

162
00:13:48,240 --> 00:13:50,320
just to keep breathing a little longer.

163
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:55,120
That's why I told you.

164
00:13:55,640 --> 00:13:57,560
It's not just black and white.

165
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:01,880
There's gray in between.

166
00:14:23,160 --> 00:14:25,800
ANGPAO

167
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:31,320
<i>We know magic isn't sorcery.</i>

168
00:14:33,280 --> 00:14:36,080
<i>A magician can only create</i>

169
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:38,840
<i>illusions</i>

170
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:42,560
<i>because they can never become real.</i>

171
00:14:46,840 --> 00:14:47,720
ANGPAO

172
00:14:48,880 --> 00:14:49,720
RISA

173
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:50,520
CHEN

174
00:14:50,600 --> 00:14:51,480
KONGKIAT

175
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:55,400
PHAYAK

176
00:14:56,880 --> 00:14:57,920
HONG

177
00:15:00,640 --> 00:15:02,240
Hunt them all down.

178
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:05,600
Hong and us,

179
00:15:05,680 --> 00:15:07,200
we've fought over her since we were young.

180
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:08,640
- Now we're old.
- Yeah.

181
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:10,720
None of us has gotten anywhere.

182
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:13,040
Maybe staying friends like this

183
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,160
is kinda nice too.

184
00:15:15,360 --> 00:15:16,200
Hey, Yak!

185
00:15:16,280 --> 00:15:18,280
Does that mean
you're finally giving up on Hong

186
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:21,000
and quitting the competition with me?

187
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:22,280
- Cheers first.
- Yeah!

188
00:15:23,080 --> 00:15:24,080
- Gao, no way.
- Huh?

189
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:25,320
You bastard.

190
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:27,200
Nice try, acting

191
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:30,480
all persuasive just now.
I know your tricks. I've got experience.

192
00:15:30,560 --> 00:15:32,560
If I had other friends,
I wouldn't hang out with you.

193
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:34,320
Oh please, and yet you still stick around!

194
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:36,200
- Come on, cheers!
- Yeah.

195
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:37,120
Cheers!

196
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:38,240
You bastard.

197
00:15:51,960 --> 00:15:52,800
Stay still!

198
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:53,920
You too. Don't move.

199
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:57,000
Or I'll blow your guts out.

200
00:15:58,600 --> 00:15:59,440
Brother.

201
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:02,200
Calm down.

202
00:16:02,280 --> 00:16:05,120
How about we talk this out first?

203
00:16:05,640 --> 00:16:07,320
You gotta take it easy, okay?

204
00:16:07,920 --> 00:16:09,400
Let me ask who you are

205
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:11,520
and what you want from us.

206
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:13,400
What do I want?

207
00:16:14,960 --> 00:16:16,440
I want your lives!

208
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:24,480
Gao!

209
00:16:25,600 --> 00:16:28,280
Don't! Gao got shot!

210
00:16:33,040 --> 00:16:34,760
Gao. Look at your face.

211
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:36,160
Who are you?

212
00:16:38,360 --> 00:16:40,760
Pae!

213
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:43,440
Pae, damn!

214
00:16:43,520 --> 00:16:44,280
I almost pissed myself.

215
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:45,800
Hey, no way.

216
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:48,040
Otherwise, I'd disgrace the name
Thousand-Face Pae.

217
00:16:49,640 --> 00:16:53,720
You got the nickname
because you're great at disguises

218
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:55,040
and fooled people
with a thousand faces, right?

219
00:16:55,880 --> 00:16:58,120
My disguises sucked.
I got beaten up so bad,

220
00:16:58,200 --> 00:17:00,000
the doctor had to wrap my whole face.

221
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:01,480
- What?
- What?

222
00:17:01,560 --> 00:17:03,520
That's a good one.

223
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:05,800
Sharp as ever. Amazing.

224
00:17:05,880 --> 00:17:06,839
Pae!

225
00:17:06,920 --> 00:17:08,520
Hey, Hong!

226
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:11,319
- Come here.
- Hey!

227
00:17:12,160 --> 00:17:14,079
Easy there, Pae.

228
00:17:15,040 --> 00:17:15,960
- Yeah.
- Hey.

229
00:17:16,040 --> 00:17:17,560
When did you get out of prison?

230
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:19,520
No clue when I got out.

231
00:17:19,599 --> 00:17:22,760
What I do know is I haven't
seen your faces in ten years.

232
00:17:22,839 --> 00:17:23,680
Yeah.

233
00:17:23,760 --> 00:17:25,839
Tonight, we drink until…

234
00:17:25,920 --> 00:17:27,760
We go completely wild!

235
00:17:27,839 --> 00:17:29,480
- Full blast tonight!
- Yeah!

236
00:17:31,760 --> 00:17:33,560
I missed you guys.

237
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:36,240
Missed you too.

238
00:17:36,320 --> 00:17:38,400
It's been so long. I really missed you.

239
00:17:38,480 --> 00:17:39,320
Sit down.

240
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:40,800
Come here. Sit, Pae.

241
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:41,760
- Come on.
- Alright.

242
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:45,080
PHAYAK

243
00:17:48,040 --> 00:17:49,240
GAO

244
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:54,240
Oh, come on.

245
00:17:54,320 --> 00:17:56,400
- Why are you standing?
- Don't feel like sitting.

246
00:17:58,120 --> 00:17:59,680
- Your hemorrhoids still acting up?
- I missed you, Hong.

247
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:11,840
<i>What do you think you are?</i>

248
00:18:12,480 --> 00:18:13,680
A hunter?

249
00:18:16,360 --> 00:18:19,480
Or maybe just prey
fooling yourself into thinking

250
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,200
you're the hunter?

251
00:18:21,280 --> 00:18:23,000
You're just prey

252
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:26,280
fooling yourself into thinking
you're the hunter.

253
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:29,400
<i>Aek.</i>

254
00:18:30,080 --> 00:18:32,000
Chai left these documents for you.

255
00:18:32,080 --> 00:18:33,080
Thanks a lot.

256
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:38,480
That knife's pretty cool.

257
00:18:40,520 --> 00:18:43,480
Nice, right? I carved it myself.

258
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:45,920
Seriously?

259
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:48,000
- Can I have it?
- Hey.

260
00:18:49,320 --> 00:18:50,440
Not this one.

261
00:18:51,120 --> 00:18:53,160
If you want one,
I'll make you another someday.

262
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:10,360
Your ice has already melted.
I'll get you a new one.

263
00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:18,880
Hey, Mix. Heard anything about Aek?

264
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:21,360
I've been trying to reach him for ages,

265
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:23,400
but no luck.

266
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:24,800
Honestly,

267
00:19:25,320 --> 00:19:27,400
after what happened
at Hyena Pub back then,

268
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:29,200
I haven't seen anyone since.

269
00:19:29,800 --> 00:19:32,200
I only heard rumors

270
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:34,040
that Aek crossed over into Cambodia.

271
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:37,400
Do you need to get in touch with him?

272
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:44,040
Nothing. Just miss him.

273
00:20:31,880 --> 00:20:35,320
You said you're mad at your dad
for leaving you.

274
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:38,720
But you still keep waiting for him here.

275
00:20:40,480 --> 00:20:42,160
If it were me, I wouldn't put up with it.

276
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:44,280
A selfish father

277
00:20:44,360 --> 00:20:48,680
who ran off and left his daughter alone
with a 20-million-baht debt.

278
00:20:52,080 --> 00:20:53,600
Forget you not understanding.

279
00:20:54,280 --> 00:20:56,360
Sometimes, I don't understand
myself either.

280
00:20:57,680 --> 00:21:00,000
No matter how angry I am,

281
00:21:02,160 --> 00:21:04,480
it never changes the fact

282
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:08,240
that Dad is the person I love most.

283
00:21:12,520 --> 00:21:14,920
Honestly, I don't really get
someone like you either.

284
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:16,440
Your family has money.

285
00:21:17,880 --> 00:21:19,480
Why do you work…

286
00:21:21,960 --> 00:21:23,720
as a scammer with us?

287
00:21:29,640 --> 00:21:30,560
Because of you.

288
00:21:39,240 --> 00:21:41,280
You said my novel was crap, right?

289
00:21:44,080 --> 00:21:46,760
Made-up, stuck in an ideal world,

290
00:21:47,280 --> 00:21:48,840
all black and white.

291
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:54,200
I needed research for my novel, I guess.

292
00:21:56,560 --> 00:21:57,840
That's all?

293
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,280
That's all I can think of for now.

294
00:22:03,320 --> 00:22:05,560
If I think of anything else,
I'll let you know.

295
00:22:25,480 --> 00:22:27,080
Excuse me, sir.

296
00:22:27,920 --> 00:22:29,760
That lady over there sent this over.

297
00:23:14,240 --> 00:23:16,320
Koh! It's really you!

298
00:23:16,840 --> 00:23:17,880
How have you been?

299
00:23:22,920 --> 00:23:24,960
Tee, your timing seriously sucks,
you know that?

300
00:23:28,560 --> 00:23:29,960
Still a flirt as always, huh?

301
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:32,640
Flirt my ass. It's just…

302
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:37,920
Forget it. So, what about you?

303
00:23:38,440 --> 00:23:39,440
Haven't seen you in forever.

304
00:23:39,520 --> 00:23:42,880
I heard the bartender
say you've been looking for Aek?

305
00:23:42,960 --> 00:23:44,120
Yeah.

306
00:23:45,240 --> 00:23:46,640
You heard something about him!?

307
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:49,360
Do you really want to know?

308
00:23:57,760 --> 00:23:58,840
This way, Koh.

309
00:24:09,840 --> 00:24:12,160
Tee, are you sure

310
00:24:12,240 --> 00:24:14,200
the guy we're meeting really knows Aek?

311
00:24:15,080 --> 00:24:17,840
Hello. We're here. What now?

312
00:24:19,280 --> 00:24:21,640
Sure. But I want cash for my cut.

313
00:24:32,240 --> 00:24:33,560
Hey.

314
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:36,960
Boss Kluay wants to see you.

315
00:24:38,840 --> 00:24:41,520
Tee, you sold me out?

316
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:43,200
Sorry, bro. I needed money.

317
00:24:43,280 --> 00:24:45,680
Boss Kluay put a huge bounty on you.

318
00:24:45,760 --> 00:24:46,880
I didn't have a choice.

319
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:51,080
Are you coming nicely,
or do you want to get hurt?

320
00:24:56,640 --> 00:24:57,760
I'm not going.

321
00:25:06,320 --> 00:25:08,240
You brat, get over here!

322
00:25:39,040 --> 00:25:40,000
You, take this!

323
00:25:50,080 --> 00:25:51,040
Come on!

324
00:25:58,800 --> 00:26:00,000
I surrender, bro.

325
00:26:01,120 --> 00:26:02,080
Can I ask something?

326
00:26:03,120 --> 00:26:06,120
You had a gun.
Why didn't you use it earlier?

327
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:08,280
- None of your damn business.
- Don't shoot yet.

328
00:26:10,240 --> 00:26:12,040
You've got a gun now.

329
00:26:13,320 --> 00:26:14,880
Shouldn't you be watching your back too?

330
00:26:22,200 --> 00:26:24,400
Could've come a little earlier, Chen.

331
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:29,800
Hey, how'd you know I was here anyway?

332
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:32,680
I didn't. A customer
told me to hurry over.

333
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:36,480
Here you go. One non-sweet

334
00:26:36,560 --> 00:26:38,680
iced cocoa with extra whipped cream.

335
00:26:38,760 --> 00:26:39,920
EIGHT HOURS EARLIER

336
00:26:44,080 --> 00:26:45,120
This is really good.

337
00:26:46,120 --> 00:26:48,480
- Really?
- Really.

338
00:26:49,840 --> 00:26:53,480
Does the shop do delivery?
So I can order sometime.

339
00:26:54,720 --> 00:26:57,800
Sorry, but we're not on any delivery apps.

340
00:26:57,880 --> 00:26:59,560
Oh, really?

341
00:27:00,280 --> 00:27:02,840
You don't even have a shop LINE account?

342
00:27:02,920 --> 00:27:05,680
How about this?
I'll give you my personal LINE.

343
00:27:05,760 --> 00:27:08,400
Just message me there
and send me your location.

344
00:27:08,480 --> 00:27:09,560
I'll deliver it myself.

345
00:27:10,080 --> 00:27:11,240
Really?

346
00:27:12,920 --> 00:27:15,840
I gave a customer my LINE
for drink orders, right?

347
00:27:15,920 --> 00:27:18,760
Then she ordered a drink
and sent me this location. Look.

348
00:27:21,160 --> 00:27:22,640
SAME ICED COCOA, PLEASE HURRY

349
00:27:30,840 --> 00:27:31,760
<i>Excuse me, sir.</i>

350
00:27:31,840 --> 00:27:33,400
That lady over there sent this over.

351
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:46,560
What?

352
00:27:46,640 --> 00:27:48,280
- What's got you so shocked?
- I got one too.

353
00:27:51,960 --> 00:27:53,800
Run. Someone's hunting you.

354
00:27:57,520 --> 00:27:58,600
What does that mean?

355
00:28:01,120 --> 00:28:02,240
Kluay knows now

356
00:28:02,760 --> 00:28:04,240
that we took his mom's money.

357
00:28:05,160 --> 00:28:07,800
We gotta get back to the shop,
grab the cash, and run.

358
00:28:11,240 --> 00:28:13,520
Hey, finish your drink! Finish it!

359
00:28:13,600 --> 00:28:15,040
You'll puke everywhere.

360
00:28:15,120 --> 00:28:16,680
- Really.
- Cheers!

361
00:28:18,200 --> 00:28:19,760
Let's keep drinking in the room.

362
00:28:19,840 --> 00:28:20,760
You wanna keep going?

363
00:28:20,840 --> 00:28:22,840
Order another bottle, Yak.

364
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:25,000
You're already dead drunk.

365
00:28:25,080 --> 00:28:26,320
Another bottle. Let's keep going.

366
00:28:26,400 --> 00:28:27,680
Enough already.

367
00:28:27,760 --> 00:28:29,000
- Get down.
- Come on.

368
00:28:29,080 --> 00:28:31,120
- Get down now!
- Go!

369
00:28:32,120 --> 00:28:35,000
I can't even get properly drunk
because I have to look after you.

370
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:37,440
Why are you such a lightweight?

371
00:28:37,520 --> 00:28:40,480
What do you mean, lightweight?
I'm still fine!

372
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:41,560
Hey.

373
00:28:41,640 --> 00:28:43,080
You're both lightweights.

374
00:28:43,600 --> 00:28:45,800
I'm out. I'm sleepy. Going to bed.

375
00:28:45,880 --> 00:28:47,440
Hong, come on.

376
00:28:47,520 --> 00:28:49,240
You barely drank anything.

377
00:28:56,240 --> 00:28:57,520
Pae!

378
00:28:58,360 --> 00:29:00,800
Enough. Stop messing around. I'm sleepy.

379
00:29:01,520 --> 00:29:02,720
Hey!

380
00:29:02,800 --> 00:29:04,720
The gas is gonna run out.

381
00:29:04,800 --> 00:29:08,040
And take off that fake beard already.
It's annoying.

382
00:29:10,600 --> 00:29:11,760
That's not a fake beard.

383
00:29:11,840 --> 00:29:13,440
Fake my ass.

384
00:29:14,480 --> 00:29:16,840
- What? Wait.
- It's real.

385
00:29:16,920 --> 00:29:19,760
Sorry. I'm sorry, babe.

386
00:29:22,920 --> 00:29:24,280
Hey, what's up, Pae?

387
00:29:24,360 --> 00:29:25,600
That's not Pae.

388
00:29:26,800 --> 00:29:28,120
Sorry, sir.

389
00:29:34,080 --> 00:29:35,520
Are you gonna tell us or not?

390
00:29:35,600 --> 00:29:37,120
I'm not telling!

391
00:29:37,200 --> 00:29:38,120
Just tell them.

392
00:29:39,200 --> 00:29:40,400
So are you telling us or not?

393
00:29:40,480 --> 00:29:43,080
Even if you beat me to death,

394
00:29:43,160 --> 00:29:45,160
I won't tell you!

395
00:29:45,240 --> 00:29:47,760
I'm begging you, just tell them!
I can't take it anymore!

396
00:29:47,840 --> 00:29:49,000
One more!

397
00:29:49,080 --> 00:29:50,920
Hey, quit screwing around.

398
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:52,680
Grip my arm a little softer.

399
00:29:54,800 --> 00:29:58,040
This time, if you don't talk,
every one of you dies!

400
00:29:59,680 --> 00:30:02,640
Room service. Your food order is here.

401
00:30:02,720 --> 00:30:03,960
What did you order?

402
00:30:04,040 --> 00:30:05,600
Nothing. I didn't order anything.

403
00:30:06,360 --> 00:30:07,280
- Gao.
- Huh?

404
00:30:07,360 --> 00:30:08,920
What did you order?

405
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:11,680
I didn't order anything. I'm drunk.

406
00:30:13,040 --> 00:30:14,920
Maybe Hong ordered it?

407
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:20,240
Probably not.

408
00:30:20,320 --> 00:30:21,760
Keep an eye on them.

409
00:30:24,520 --> 00:30:25,600
Stay quiet.

410
00:30:28,840 --> 00:30:30,840
- Room service.
- We didn't order anything.

411
00:30:30,920 --> 00:30:34,560
Room 232, correct?

412
00:30:35,080 --> 00:30:36,720
Then leave it outside the room.

413
00:30:36,800 --> 00:30:39,440
Wait. No, sir.

414
00:30:39,520 --> 00:30:41,400
I sincerely apologize.

415
00:30:41,480 --> 00:30:45,000
Hotel policy requires us to hand
the food directly to the guest.

416
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:46,760
Last time, there was an incident

417
00:30:46,840 --> 00:30:48,960
where food was left outside a room,
and cockroaches got into it.

418
00:30:49,040 --> 00:30:51,080
The guest complained
that it was the hotel's fault.

419
00:30:51,160 --> 00:30:52,880
What a hassle.

420
00:30:52,960 --> 00:30:54,480
Fine. Get in here. Hurry up.

421
00:30:54,560 --> 00:30:55,760
Yes.Yes, sir.

422
00:31:01,560 --> 00:31:02,880
I'll take payment now, please.

423
00:31:02,960 --> 00:31:05,640
The total is 6,990 baht.

424
00:31:06,360 --> 00:31:07,400
Why is it so expensive?

425
00:31:07,480 --> 00:31:10,400
The 1987 Château de Maria wine alone

426
00:31:10,480 --> 00:31:11,680
costs 3,890 baht.

427
00:31:11,760 --> 00:31:14,240
The medium-rare T-bone steak
is 1,250 baht.

428
00:31:14,320 --> 00:31:16,240
- And there is--
- Alright, enough.

429
00:31:16,320 --> 00:31:17,160
This is exactly why

430
00:31:17,240 --> 00:31:19,000
you blew through all the boss's money.

431
00:31:20,960 --> 00:31:22,600
Go pay for it yourself.

432
00:31:23,200 --> 00:31:24,640
- Go on.
- Yes.

433
00:31:24,720 --> 00:31:26,320
Not sure if I have enough cash.

434
00:31:31,120 --> 00:31:33,160
Thank you. Please take the bill as well.

435
00:31:33,240 --> 00:31:34,120
Sure.

436
00:31:35,800 --> 00:31:37,800
IN 20 SECONDS, THE LIGHTS WILL GO OUT!

437
00:31:39,320 --> 00:31:40,920
IN 20 SECONDS, THE LIGHTS WILL GO OUT!

438
00:31:41,520 --> 00:31:43,280
Start counting after the room door closes.

439
00:31:43,880 --> 00:31:44,760
What are you talking about?

440
00:31:46,080 --> 00:31:48,040
Enjoy your meal. Thank you very much.

441
00:31:48,120 --> 00:31:49,080
Oh, the bill.

442
00:31:58,440 --> 00:31:59,800
What a waste of time.

443
00:32:00,320 --> 00:32:01,440
Calm down, bro.

444
00:32:01,520 --> 00:32:03,160
- Let me eat first.
- What now?

445
00:32:03,240 --> 00:32:04,800
And have some wine.

446
00:32:04,880 --> 00:32:05,960
Are you gonna talk or not?

447
00:32:06,040 --> 00:32:07,160
Can I at least have some wine

448
00:32:07,240 --> 00:32:08,920
and enjoy myself for a bit?

449
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:11,320
So I can die happy.

450
00:32:12,440 --> 00:32:14,880
Where'd the bottle opener go?

451
00:32:14,960 --> 00:32:17,200
Do you have anything
I can use to pry this open?

452
00:32:17,280 --> 00:32:19,320
Once I'm done drinking,

453
00:32:19,400 --> 00:32:21,360
you can shoot me right away. Six.

454
00:32:21,440 --> 00:32:23,960
- Five, bro. Four, three.
- What are you counting?

455
00:32:24,040 --> 00:32:25,960
Two. Lotto numbers for you. One, zero.

456
00:32:57,560 --> 00:32:59,360
KANCHANAPHISEK ROAD, BANG BUA THONG

457
00:33:16,720 --> 00:33:18,160
Ris, watch out.

458
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:03,680
I just came to warn you.
You'd better not go back to the room.

459
00:34:04,440 --> 00:34:07,000
Boss Kluay knows about all of you now.

460
00:34:07,640 --> 00:34:08,679
What do you mean?

461
00:34:09,560 --> 00:34:10,920
Consider yourself warned.

462
00:34:17,840 --> 00:34:18,920
Wait.

463
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:20,400
Who are you?

464
00:34:21,480 --> 00:34:22,440
Why are you telling us this?

465
00:34:22,520 --> 00:34:24,560
Next time we meet,

466
00:34:25,080 --> 00:34:26,199
I'll explain.

467
00:34:49,960 --> 00:34:51,120
That woman was telling the truth.

468
00:34:51,199 --> 00:34:52,320
That means

469
00:34:52,400 --> 00:34:55,199
this Boss Kluay guy
probably knows we took his money.

470
00:34:57,000 --> 00:34:59,080
Wait, Risa. Where are you going?

471
00:34:59,160 --> 00:35:00,360
I have to go back in.

472
00:35:00,960 --> 00:35:02,400
I have over a million hidden in there.

473
00:35:02,480 --> 00:35:04,280
I hope they haven't found it.

474
00:35:21,400 --> 00:35:24,120
Damn it! They've taken all the money!

475
00:35:25,200 --> 00:35:27,920
Risa, hurry. They might come back.

476
00:35:32,080 --> 00:35:35,320
NO WRITING OR POSTING NOTICES

477
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:38,560
- I told you these brats would come back.
- Risa.

478
00:35:38,640 --> 00:35:39,480
Hey!

479
00:35:39,560 --> 00:35:41,120
- Stop!
- Run!

480
00:35:44,600 --> 00:35:45,760
Ris, come on.

481
00:35:47,360 --> 00:35:48,440
Stop!

482
00:35:54,600 --> 00:35:55,840
This way!

483
00:35:55,920 --> 00:35:56,800
Go!

484
00:35:56,880 --> 00:35:57,920
Hurry up!

485
00:35:58,000 --> 00:35:58,960
What are they?

486
00:36:08,640 --> 00:36:09,880
Take the other way down.

487
00:36:22,400 --> 00:36:23,560
What's up, Angpao?

488
00:36:23,640 --> 00:36:25,920
<i>Hello, Ris, Mung!</i>

489
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:28,360
<i>Help me. I don't know where I am.</i>

490
00:36:28,440 --> 00:36:31,120
Wait, Angpao. Calm down. Speak slowly.

491
00:36:31,200 --> 00:36:32,720
I can't understand you.

492
00:36:32,800 --> 00:36:35,000
<i>They broke into my room</i>
<i>and trashed the whole place.</i>

493
00:36:35,080 --> 00:36:36,680
<i>They beat me up and took the money too.</i>

494
00:36:36,760 --> 00:36:38,600
<i>They were gonna kidnap me,</i>

495
00:36:38,680 --> 00:36:40,560
<i>but luckily, someone saved me.</i>

496
00:36:40,640 --> 00:36:41,800
Where are you now?

497
00:36:43,280 --> 00:36:46,680
I don't know. I passed out,
and I don't remember anything.

498
00:36:46,760 --> 00:36:49,480
<i>When I woke up, I was here.</i>

499
00:36:50,360 --> 00:36:52,640
It's so damn dark here, Ris.

500
00:36:54,960 --> 00:36:57,520
Hello? Ris.

501
00:36:57,600 --> 00:36:59,720
My battery's dying.
I already shared my location.

502
00:36:59,800 --> 00:37:00,760
<i>Hurry and come find--</i>

503
00:37:00,840 --> 00:37:02,160
- Hello, Pao?
- Pao!

504
00:37:02,240 --> 00:37:06,600
Hello? Hello? Hello?

505
00:37:06,680 --> 00:37:09,280
He said he shared his location, right?

506
00:37:11,240 --> 00:37:13,520
I don't know where this is.

507
00:37:13,600 --> 00:37:15,080
Let's go. We'll figure it out.

508
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:30,920
Oh no. Damn it.

509
00:37:32,320 --> 00:37:33,160
Let's go.

510
00:37:33,240 --> 00:37:34,440
Koh.

511
00:37:36,160 --> 00:37:37,160
No way.

512
00:37:39,240 --> 00:37:41,240
The safe. What about the safe?

513
00:37:41,320 --> 00:37:42,640
Where is it?

514
00:37:51,960 --> 00:37:53,240
Koh!

515
00:37:54,680 --> 00:37:57,760
Koh, let's go after them!

516
00:37:57,840 --> 00:37:59,600
If we die, we die. I don't care anymore.

517
00:37:59,680 --> 00:38:00,880
Calm down, Chen.

518
00:38:01,480 --> 00:38:02,640
Let's get the money out first.

519
00:38:02,720 --> 00:38:05,800
Then we'll regroup and make a plan.
We can go after them anytime.

520
00:38:14,920 --> 00:38:15,760
Hello.

521
00:38:16,480 --> 00:38:19,840
Hello, Mr. Koh. Do you remember me?

522
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:23,880
<i>Our mothers live at the same nursing home.</i>

523
00:38:24,560 --> 00:38:26,400
Is that damn Boss Kluay?

524
00:38:28,200 --> 00:38:29,240
What do you want?

525
00:38:29,840 --> 00:38:31,960
I want payback.

526
00:38:33,160 --> 00:38:35,040
Don't think you can mess with me

527
00:38:35,760 --> 00:38:37,240
and get away with it.

528
00:38:37,320 --> 00:38:41,240
I saw the clip. I know
what you did to my mother.

529
00:38:42,440 --> 00:38:43,480
What clip?

530
00:38:44,120 --> 00:38:45,440
You're going to pay.

531
00:38:46,880 --> 00:38:50,400
Hope you enjoy the new menu
I've prepared for you.

532
00:38:53,400 --> 00:38:54,880
Hey! Hello?

533
00:38:57,840 --> 00:38:59,760
What new menu?

534
00:39:09,760 --> 00:39:11,040
Hurry up.

535
00:39:14,440 --> 00:39:15,960
He took all the money.

536
00:39:25,360 --> 00:39:27,480
Hey, Koh, wait.

537
00:39:27,560 --> 00:39:29,240
What's in there?

538
00:39:34,040 --> 00:39:35,280
That's Kluay's new menu!

539
00:39:35,360 --> 00:39:36,880
- Move! Run, Chen!
- Go!

540
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:50,840
Chen.

541
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:27,280
What do we do now?

542
00:40:28,080 --> 00:40:30,840
Find out where he is.
Then we go after him.

543
00:40:31,960 --> 00:40:33,560
You're gonna get us both killed, Chen.

544
00:40:34,080 --> 00:40:36,480
Then we die. I'll die with him.

545
00:40:36,560 --> 00:40:38,640
Chen, can you calm down for one second?

546
00:40:39,160 --> 00:40:40,400
Just let me think.

547
00:40:47,440 --> 00:40:50,000
The customer sent another location.

548
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:53,080
What's this now?

549
00:40:58,240 --> 00:41:00,200
I haven't even delivered
the first order yet.

550
00:41:01,920 --> 00:41:05,160
You still don't get it?
She isn't some ordinary customer.

551
00:41:06,120 --> 00:41:07,200
What do you mean?

552
00:41:08,200 --> 00:41:09,240
You'll figure it out soon enough.

553
00:41:10,080 --> 00:41:11,280
Here.

554
00:41:11,360 --> 00:41:12,280
Just guide me there.

555
00:41:12,360 --> 00:41:13,280
Where are you going?

556
00:41:13,880 --> 00:41:15,800
To the location she sent us.

557
00:41:53,680 --> 00:41:55,520
I think Angpao's here.

558
00:41:55,600 --> 00:41:57,760
Let's hurry. I'm worried about him.

559
00:41:57,840 --> 00:41:58,920
Hold on.

560
00:42:04,480 --> 00:42:05,520
Let's go.

561
00:42:27,720 --> 00:42:30,280
We should kill the lights
in case Boss Kluay's men are here.

562
00:43:13,560 --> 00:43:14,840
I'm gonna kill you! You're dead!

563
00:43:14,920 --> 00:43:17,320
I'm gonna kill you!

564
00:43:18,520 --> 00:43:19,440
Angpao!

565
00:43:23,600 --> 00:43:25,040
- Ris.
- Pao?

566
00:43:25,120 --> 00:43:26,240
Mung!

567
00:43:28,080 --> 00:43:29,600
Angpao.

568
00:43:29,680 --> 00:43:31,360
Are you okay? Are you hurt?

569
00:43:31,440 --> 00:43:32,680
I'm okay.

570
00:43:32,760 --> 00:43:35,120
If you're okay, let go of me.
I can't breathe.

571
00:43:35,960 --> 00:43:36,880
Let go.

572
00:43:37,680 --> 00:43:38,680
Wait, Angpao.

573
00:43:38,760 --> 00:43:41,040
What exactly happened to you?

574
00:43:44,520 --> 00:43:46,200
Hide!

575
00:43:49,240 --> 00:43:50,760
Don't you think this is weird?

576
00:43:50,840 --> 00:43:53,080
Why would the customer have us
deliver cocoa to a place like this?

577
00:43:54,560 --> 00:43:56,040
You still don't get it?

578
00:43:56,120 --> 00:43:59,120
That girl isn't some ordinary customer.

579
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:01,080
What do you mean?

580
00:44:06,800 --> 00:44:08,720
What was that?

581
00:44:19,800 --> 00:44:21,920
- Was that a cat?
- Was that really a cat?

582
00:44:22,520 --> 00:44:23,680
Definitely a cat.

583
00:44:28,200 --> 00:44:29,840
This place really is weird.

584
00:44:29,920 --> 00:44:31,480
Let's check somewhere else. Come on.

585
00:44:34,240 --> 00:44:35,800
Did the customer
send me the wrong location?

586
00:44:47,280 --> 00:44:50,720
People still fall for tricks like that?

587
00:44:50,800 --> 00:44:54,200
Either your cat impression was amazing
or those guys are really stupid.

588
00:44:54,280 --> 00:44:55,760
It was good.

589
00:44:56,600 --> 00:44:57,480
Keep it down.

590
00:44:57,560 --> 00:44:59,000
I found them.

591
00:44:59,080 --> 00:45:00,240
Drop it.

592
00:45:07,800 --> 00:45:09,760
You really need a gun for this?

593
00:45:09,840 --> 00:45:11,840
How was I supposed to know
it was you, miss?

594
00:45:14,280 --> 00:45:15,840
Hey, what are you doing here?

595
00:45:15,920 --> 00:45:17,280
What are you guys doing here?

596
00:45:17,360 --> 00:45:18,520
We're just…

597
00:45:21,160 --> 00:45:22,120
Mung!

598
00:45:22,200 --> 00:45:24,560
There's something red on your head.

599
00:45:26,200 --> 00:45:27,680
You've got some on your cheek too.

600
00:45:27,760 --> 00:45:29,960
Really? Where?

601
00:45:37,000 --> 00:45:38,360
Don't move

602
00:45:38,440 --> 00:45:39,760
if you don't want to die.

603
00:45:46,080 --> 00:45:47,120
Don't shoot.

604
00:45:48,360 --> 00:45:49,240
I surrender.

605
00:45:57,360 --> 00:45:58,280
Stay still.

606
00:45:58,360 --> 00:46:00,640
Take it easy.

607
00:46:00,720 --> 00:46:02,720
Hey, it's you guys?

608
00:46:02,800 --> 00:46:04,880
Oh, Sis Hong?

609
00:46:04,960 --> 00:46:07,640
- I thought it was someone else.
- You idiots.

610
00:46:07,720 --> 00:46:10,920
You scared me. I thought
we were about to shoot each other.

611
00:46:12,920 --> 00:46:14,800
What is this, a reunion?

612
00:46:15,320 --> 00:46:18,480
Hey, did you guys kidnap Angpao?

613
00:46:18,560 --> 00:46:21,640
Kidnap him? We can barely save ourselves.

614
00:46:23,000 --> 00:46:26,520
So Boss Kluay really is after us.

615
00:46:26,600 --> 00:46:28,760
- Wait. Can I ask something?
- Yeah.

616
00:46:29,360 --> 00:46:30,920
Who sent us the location?

617
00:46:31,560 --> 00:46:35,040
If it wasn't you guys, then who was it?

618
00:46:48,320 --> 00:46:49,360
No, not this.

619
00:46:50,560 --> 00:46:51,880
It came from over there.

620
00:47:02,400 --> 00:47:04,120
Looks like we're finally
getting some answers.

621
00:47:25,120 --> 00:47:27,360
<i>Welcome, everyone.</i>

622
00:47:27,440 --> 00:47:30,360
<i>I know each of you very well.</i>

623
00:47:33,520 --> 00:47:36,720
<i>But you don't need to know who I am.</i>

624
00:47:37,640 --> 00:47:40,960
<i>From now on, call me Admin.</i>

625
00:47:41,560 --> 00:47:43,520
<i>Let's get straight to the point.</i>

626
00:47:43,600 --> 00:47:46,160
<i>Right now, Boss Kluay,</i>

627
00:47:46,240 --> 00:47:49,520
<i>the one you all tricked</i>
<i>into taking the money,</i>

628
00:47:49,600 --> 00:47:52,280
<i>is hunting you down.</i>

629
00:47:52,800 --> 00:47:56,640
<i>That's why I called you all here today,</i>

630
00:47:57,560 --> 00:48:00,480
<i>to make you an offer.</i>

631
00:48:01,240 --> 00:48:02,440
<i>An offer</i>

632
00:48:02,520 --> 00:48:05,920
<i>that will turn all of you from prey</i>

633
00:48:06,000 --> 00:48:07,400
<i>into hunters.</i>

634
00:48:09,480 --> 00:48:13,040
<i>All you have to do</i>
<i>is follow the plan I've prepared.</i>

635
00:48:13,120 --> 00:48:14,840
<i>Once Boss Kluay is dealt with,</i>

636
00:48:14,920 --> 00:48:19,240
<i>every one of you</i>
<i>will receive a reward big enough</i>

637
00:48:19,320 --> 00:48:22,160
<i>to make you forget</i>
<i>all the money you just lost.</i>

638
00:48:29,680 --> 00:48:32,840
If you've got guts,
come out and talk face-to-face.

639
00:48:32,920 --> 00:48:34,880
You can't just talk to yourself

640
00:48:34,960 --> 00:48:36,680
and call this a negotiation.

641
00:48:36,760 --> 00:48:38,720
Come out here. Come out.

642
00:48:38,800 --> 00:48:41,320
Hey, why are you yelling?

643
00:48:48,400 --> 00:48:50,960
This is just a video recording.

644
00:48:51,720 --> 00:48:54,600
No one here, including me,

645
00:48:55,240 --> 00:48:56,400
can contact Admin.

646
00:49:07,880 --> 00:49:09,160
Just message me there.

647
00:49:10,120 --> 00:49:11,000
Perfect.

648
00:49:11,080 --> 00:49:12,960
Start counting after the room door closes.

649
00:49:13,840 --> 00:49:16,480
I just came to warn you.
You'd better not go back to the room.

650
00:49:19,480 --> 00:49:21,040
Hey! You're the customer!

651
00:49:21,720 --> 00:49:22,920
She's the one who saved me.

652
00:49:24,360 --> 00:49:27,200
My name's Lin. I'm Admin's assistant.

653
00:49:27,280 --> 00:49:28,480
Then who is Admin?

654
00:49:28,560 --> 00:49:29,680
I don't know either.

655
00:49:30,400 --> 00:49:33,840
Honestly, I was contacted
just like all of you.

656
00:49:33,920 --> 00:49:35,640
The only difference is, my job

657
00:49:35,720 --> 00:49:38,480
is to explain Admin's plan to you.

658
00:49:38,560 --> 00:49:40,960
I'm the middleman between you and Admin,

659
00:49:41,040 --> 00:49:43,640
making sure the plan succeeds.

660
00:49:44,480 --> 00:49:47,600
And why should we work with you?

661
00:49:47,680 --> 00:49:49,680
If Admin hadn't sent me to help today,

662
00:49:49,760 --> 00:49:51,920
what do you think
would've happened to all of you?

663
00:49:54,480 --> 00:49:57,240
Just take down Boss Kluay.
Follow Admin's plan.

664
00:49:57,320 --> 00:49:59,320
You get rid of your enemy

665
00:49:59,400 --> 00:50:01,240
and get paid a fortune too.

666
00:50:02,520 --> 00:50:03,520
Don't overthink it.

667
00:50:03,600 --> 00:50:06,360
I don't think any of you
really have much of a choice.

668
00:50:08,880 --> 00:50:10,040
What exactly

669
00:50:11,040 --> 00:50:11,920
is this plan?

670
00:50:12,000 --> 00:50:13,640
I'll tell you the whole plan

671
00:50:13,720 --> 00:50:15,720
once every one of you

672
00:50:15,800 --> 00:50:17,160
agrees.

673
00:50:18,520 --> 00:50:21,080
It's your choice.

674
00:50:21,160 --> 00:50:22,720
Work together,

675
00:50:23,320 --> 00:50:25,200
or go up against Boss Kluay on your own.

676
00:50:35,520 --> 00:50:36,440
I'm in.

677
00:50:36,520 --> 00:50:38,080
Chen.

678
00:50:38,160 --> 00:50:39,280
Aren't you going to think about it?

679
00:50:39,360 --> 00:50:41,160
This Admin guy is shady as hell.

680
00:50:41,240 --> 00:50:42,640
I don't need to think.

681
00:50:43,360 --> 00:50:45,760
Even without Admin, I'm going after him.

682
00:50:45,840 --> 00:50:47,400
He blew up my shop.

683
00:50:48,640 --> 00:50:51,360
I'm in too. I want my money back.

684
00:50:52,480 --> 00:50:55,560
If Ris is in, I'm in too.

685
00:50:56,640 --> 00:50:58,080
What about you, Mung?

686
00:50:58,160 --> 00:51:00,480
What choice do I have?
That's already two votes.

687
00:51:00,560 --> 00:51:01,880
We're in too.

688
00:51:02,400 --> 00:51:05,480
Hong, shouldn't we
talk this through first?

689
00:51:05,560 --> 00:51:08,280
What's there to discuss? This sounds fun.

690
00:51:08,360 --> 00:51:11,280
Don't you feel like we're
some kind of cool gang?

691
00:51:12,040 --> 00:51:14,400
Besides, we're already old.

692
00:51:14,480 --> 00:51:16,280
We've got nothing left to lose.

693
00:51:16,360 --> 00:51:18,520
Hong makes a good point. I support you.

694
00:51:20,640 --> 00:51:21,920
Seeing you brings me back
to my younger days.

695
00:51:22,800 --> 00:51:24,240
I haven't dressed like that in ages.

696
00:51:29,160 --> 00:51:32,280
Then we're just waiting
for your answer now, Mr. Koh.

697
00:51:40,120 --> 00:51:41,920
Fine. I'm in.

698
00:51:42,000 --> 00:51:43,120
You act way too cool.

699
00:51:43,200 --> 00:51:44,080
Yes!

700
00:51:45,440 --> 00:51:48,000
So what exactly is this plan?

701
00:51:55,280 --> 00:51:58,240
<i>Boss Kluay, a well-connected</i>
<i>boxing promoter,</i>

702
00:51:58,920 --> 00:52:00,640
<i>owner of a famous boxing gym,</i>

703
00:52:00,720 --> 00:52:03,040
<i>and a major shareholder</i>
<i>of K Fight Stadium.</i>

704
00:52:03,120 --> 00:52:06,720
<i>He's one of the godfathers</i>
<i>of the boxing world.</i>

705
00:52:06,800 --> 00:52:10,120
<i>But behind that public image,</i>
<i>his hands are far from clean.</i>

706
00:52:10,760 --> 00:52:13,320
<i>Most of his income comes</i>

707
00:52:13,400 --> 00:52:15,040
- <i>from illegal lending</i>
- That's amazing!

708
00:52:15,120 --> 00:52:17,480
<i>and underground businesses,</i>
<i>such as money laundering,</i>

709
00:52:17,560 --> 00:52:19,960
<i>fight gambling, and human trafficking.</i>

710
00:52:20,960 --> 00:52:25,440
<i>The reason he fears no one</i>
<i>is because he has powerful backing.</i>

711
00:52:25,520 --> 00:52:27,920
<i>His backer is Louis.</i>

712
00:52:28,960 --> 00:52:32,920
<i>Louis has people</i>
<i>doing his dirty work all the time.</i>

713
00:52:33,000 --> 00:52:35,520
<i>Boss Kluay is just a small pawn.</i>

714
00:52:35,600 --> 00:52:39,480
<i>He has to hand over 50% of his earnings</i>
<i>to Louis every month</i>

715
00:52:39,560 --> 00:52:42,120
<i>in exchange for protection.</i>

716
00:52:42,200 --> 00:52:43,800
<i>But at the same time,</i>

717
00:52:43,880 --> 00:52:47,160
<i>that's the weakness</i>
<i>we're going to use to bring him down.</i>

718
00:52:48,160 --> 00:52:51,560
Admin's plan is to use all your skills

719
00:52:51,640 --> 00:52:54,280
to set up a boxing bet for Boss Kluay,
the thing he knows best.

720
00:52:54,880 --> 00:52:57,400
Make him believe
he's about to win a massive payout

721
00:52:57,480 --> 00:53:00,720
until he puts up the money
he's been saving for Louis.

722
00:53:00,800 --> 00:53:03,120
And the moment he brings that money out…

723
00:53:03,200 --> 00:53:04,680
That money disappears

724
00:53:04,760 --> 00:53:06,200
and ends up with us instead.

725
00:53:07,800 --> 00:53:10,680
Once he can't pay Louis,
the trust between them will fall apart.

726
00:53:10,760 --> 00:53:13,000
Then all we have to do is sit back

727
00:53:13,080 --> 00:53:14,920
and watch the dogs tear each other apart.

728
00:53:17,240 --> 00:53:19,320
The first thing you need to do

729
00:53:20,000 --> 00:53:22,160
is create the bait.

730
00:53:22,240 --> 00:53:23,600
Boss!

731
00:53:23,680 --> 00:53:24,800
Incoming call.

732
00:53:24,880 --> 00:53:26,000
Who is it?

733
00:53:26,080 --> 00:53:28,120
Hey, hold on a second.

734
00:53:29,560 --> 00:53:30,560
Hello.

735
00:53:32,480 --> 00:53:35,160
Hong, you've still got the nerve
to call me?

736
00:53:35,240 --> 00:53:37,400
Come on, boss. I'm truly sorry.

737
00:53:37,480 --> 00:53:40,320
About your mother,
I didn't know any better.

738
00:53:40,400 --> 00:53:41,880
Please forgive me.

739
00:53:41,960 --> 00:53:43,800
<i>Even if you kill me,</i>

740
00:53:43,880 --> 00:53:45,400
<i>you still won't get your money back.</i>

741
00:53:45,480 --> 00:53:47,720
If you're calling to beg for your life,
hang up.

742
00:53:47,800 --> 00:53:50,520
All of you are going to end up buried
under a mango tree anyway.

743
00:53:51,240 --> 00:53:53,240
I'm not calling to beg for my life.

744
00:53:53,320 --> 00:53:55,440
I'm calling to ask for a chance, boss.

745
00:53:56,080 --> 00:53:57,600
Right now,

746
00:53:57,680 --> 00:54:01,720
I've found a way to get your money back.

747
00:54:05,640 --> 00:54:06,960
Go on.

748
00:54:08,600 --> 00:54:09,800
His name is Jackie Wong.

749
00:54:09,880 --> 00:54:13,680
Or as people in the industry call him,
Mr. Wong.

750
00:54:14,880 --> 00:54:18,480
<i>He's a boxing promoter</i>
<i>and gym owner from China.</i>

751
00:54:19,120 --> 00:54:22,400
<i>Besides being crazy about boxing,</i>
<i>he's also addicted to gambling.</i>

752
00:54:22,480 --> 00:54:24,040
<i>One or two million per match</i>

753
00:54:24,120 --> 00:54:25,760
<i>is pocket change to him.</i>

754
00:54:25,840 --> 00:54:27,720
Right now, he's in Thailand.

755
00:54:27,800 --> 00:54:30,320
If you're interested,
I can introduce you to him.

756
00:54:30,400 --> 00:54:32,120
Wait, how do you know him?

757
00:54:32,200 --> 00:54:33,400
Hey.

758
00:54:33,480 --> 00:54:35,200
I'm hard to resist.

759
00:54:35,280 --> 00:54:36,240
He's totally into me.

760
00:54:36,320 --> 00:54:38,640
<i>I'm actually on my way</i>
<i>to see him at his hotel right now.</i>

761
00:54:39,160 --> 00:54:41,200
Check if there are any photos
of him with Hong.

762
00:54:45,160 --> 00:54:47,280
How am I supposed to believe
what you're saying is true?

763
00:54:48,160 --> 00:54:49,120
Boss.

764
00:54:49,200 --> 00:54:52,920
You're a well-connected man.
One quick check and you'll know.

765
00:54:53,600 --> 00:54:54,800
Boss.

766
00:54:54,880 --> 00:54:58,520
I know you've got fighters
you can make win or lose on command.

767
00:54:58,600 --> 00:55:00,400
<i>Work with me,</i>

768
00:55:00,480 --> 00:55:02,680
<i>and I guarantee I'll clear my debt,</i>

769
00:55:02,760 --> 00:55:05,160
<i>with plenty left over for you to tip me.</i>

770
00:55:05,240 --> 00:55:09,400
The pig's already on the chopping block.
Cut it now, or miss your chance.

771
00:55:12,360 --> 00:55:13,640
Let me think about it.

772
00:55:15,840 --> 00:55:17,240
Hey.

773
00:55:17,320 --> 00:55:18,960
We're still missing one more photo.

774
00:55:19,040 --> 00:55:19,840
More?

775
00:55:20,800 --> 00:55:22,120
Come on, Pae. Change clothes.

776
00:55:22,200 --> 00:55:23,640
- Wait!
- Come on!

777
00:55:23,720 --> 00:55:24,520
Geez!

778
00:55:24,600 --> 00:55:26,080
- Hurry up!
- I said I don't want to do this!

779
00:55:44,640 --> 00:55:45,680
PHOTO

780
00:55:47,560 --> 00:55:48,440
Guys.

781
00:55:48,520 --> 00:55:50,800
Can you act a little closer?

782
00:55:50,880 --> 00:55:52,920
If Boss Kluay doesn't believe it,
I'm not taking responsibility.

783
00:55:54,520 --> 00:55:55,320
Just a little.

784
00:55:56,840 --> 00:55:58,440
Alright, okay.

785
00:55:58,520 --> 00:56:01,040
- You're hugging her?
- Pae, you're going too far.

786
00:56:02,920 --> 00:56:05,360
Whoa, come here! Give me your hand.

787
00:56:05,440 --> 00:56:06,920
Put it here.

788
00:56:07,000 --> 00:56:08,720
- Yeah, good.
- Bring your face closer.

789
00:56:10,360 --> 00:56:11,120
Alright, great.

790
00:56:11,200 --> 00:56:12,600
Okay, nice!

791
00:56:12,680 --> 00:56:13,800
Wow, perfect.

792
00:56:13,880 --> 00:56:15,040
Change pose.

793
00:56:15,120 --> 00:56:16,640
Kiss my cheek.

794
00:56:16,720 --> 00:56:17,800
Did you get it?

795
00:56:19,600 --> 00:56:20,360
FORMAT

796
00:56:23,880 --> 00:56:25,200
Even if we get caught,

797
00:56:25,280 --> 00:56:27,080
I don't think we'll end up in jail.

798
00:56:27,160 --> 00:56:29,200
We're running off
to live the good life, right?

799
00:56:29,280 --> 00:56:30,520
We'll get shot dead!

800
00:56:30,600 --> 00:56:33,240
<i>We need to take out Kluay first.</i>
<i>That's the only way to save those kids.</i>

801
00:56:33,320 --> 00:56:36,120
If we move too fast and go off-plan,
we'll all end up dead.

802
00:56:36,200 --> 00:56:37,960
<i>Your girl Coco,</i>

803
00:56:38,040 --> 00:56:39,320
<i>she's just a call girl.</i>

804
00:56:39,400 --> 00:56:41,320
An escort. You know that, right?

805
00:56:42,440 --> 00:56:43,880
Chen, no!

806
00:56:43,960 --> 00:56:45,640
<i>Big guy like you, what a joke!</i>

807
00:56:47,120 --> 00:56:48,680
Didn't you work this out
with Pae beforehand?

808
00:56:48,760 --> 00:56:50,600
I did. I just didn't think Pae

809
00:56:50,680 --> 00:56:52,240
would take it this far.

810
00:56:52,320 --> 00:56:55,520
Why don't we make things more interesting?

811
00:56:56,720 --> 00:56:57,760
Fight!

812
00:57:05,080 --> 00:57:06,000
Chen!

813
00:57:06,080 --> 00:57:07,360
Four!

814
00:57:07,440 --> 00:57:08,560
Chen!

815
